<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15981&amp;p=196651#p196651"><![CDATA[
Let me get this straight: this is hack, not a homebrew, right? The Action 52 games are notoriously glitchy, and you can't simply make bad physics and collision detection good, those systems are badly designed at the core. If you want the game to be good, you'd be better off coding it from the ground up in a way that doesn't suck. The graphics are cool, and it looks like this could be a good game if it wasn't so glitchy and slow.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu May 25, 2017 2:59 pm</p><hr />
